2. **🔴 Layout Bug - Container Overflow**: The `article.featured` and `div.featured` containers have **1920px width** (far exceeding the 1280px viewport). This is a horizontal overflow bug.

3. **🔴 Layout Bug - Disproportionate content ratio**: With the short article title "Get started with Alpine" and brief description, the right-side text content only fills ~100px vertically while the image is 376-576px tall. The large blank white area on the right side makes the layout appear unbalanced.

4. **The image size is NOT fixed consistently** - it's driven by the image's natural 1024px width × 9/16 aspect ratio = 576px height. This means image size would change if different featured article images had different intrinsic dimensions.

The featured article image cover does NOT maintain a consistent, reasonable fixed size - it displays at full natural image dimensions (1024×576), which is too large and causes layout imbalance.

